<subSubSection id="A4B3EFB8E925FF8FFF1DFCC2FBCFFC51" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EC16BC33E925FF8FFF1DFCC2FBCFFC51" blockId="23.[120,1225,835,1310]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
DIAGNOSIS: Yellow to pale brown, average thorax length 1.02 (
<specimenCount id="FAAF77BAE925FF8FFC24FCC5FC1EFCFC" box="[912,936,835,862]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) to 1.14 (
<specimenCount id="FAAF77BAE925FF8FFBABFCC5FB81FCFC" box="[1055,1079,835,862]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
) mm; arista with 4-2 dorsal-ventral branches; most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E925FF8FFD0EFCEFFC1DFC21" authority="Sturtevant" authorityName="Sturtevant" box="[698,939,873,899]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E925FF8FFD0EFCEFFC9CFC21" box="[698,810,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">bromeliae</emphasis>
Sturtevant
</taxonomicName>
but differs most notably by the aedeagal shaft in 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E925FF8FFE3BFC09FDA9FC0B" authorityName="Pavan and Cunha" authorityYear="1947" box="[399,543,911,937]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromelioides">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E925FF8FFE3BFC09FDA9FC0B" box="[399,543,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">bromelioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nearly straight in lateral view (vs. acutely bent, sometimes at 90°); distiphallus slightly shorter, wider, anteroventral margin more lobate in 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E925FF8FFB85FC32FB77FC6C" authorityName="Pavan and Cunha" authorityYear="1947" box="[1073,1217,948,974]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromelioides">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E925FF8FFB85FC32FB77FC6C" box="[1073,1217,948,974]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">bromelioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; oviscapt 300–320 µm, spermatheca higher than wide, introvert ca. 0.6× capsule length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
